An Ohio family has been devastated after a 15-year-old girl learning how to drive was killed Sunday when her car was hit by a train, her father and sisters were also injured in the crash.

Sierra Thornton, of Ravenna, was driving with her father and four sisters aged seven to 13-years-old when a train collided with her car at an unmarked railroad crossing. She had just earned her learner’s permit and was learning to drive.

Her father and four sisters were injured in the horrific crash, according to reports. The father and three of the younger sibnlings suffered only minor injuries and have been released from a local hospital. One is still hospitalized.

